This paper discusses the secure and efficient processing of data queries in the cloud, which is a topic that falls under the database (cs.DB) and security and privacy (cs.CR) sub-categories. The paper also proposes a new algorithm for processing range queries, which involves indexing techniques and multidimensional ranges, indicating a possible fit with the data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of random noise injection and random projection, which are techniques that can be applied in the context of cryptography (cs.CY) and software engineering (cs.SE).
